data.description: Charming beach house just 5-blocks to the Grand Pacific on a huge lot! Ask about the VA Assumable loan at 2.375% interest rate! Home is completely remodeled w/exquisite coastal decor and the solar panels are paid-off. Wood plank porcelain tile floors, smooth ceilings, recessed lighting, plantation shutters, and dual pane windows thru-out. Sparkly kitchen w/white shaker cabinets, shimmery jade backsplash, Frigidaire SS appliances, SS Farmhouse sink, granite counters. Step down into an oversized Family Room w/tongue and groove white plank wood ceiling & custom fan. Step down into the gorgeous master bedroom w/a white brick, gas fireplace w/a long mantel & shelf. Bedroom #4 is a secondary master with glass French doors to the gigantic back yard and a full-bath. Exterior stucco is Rhino Shield with a 25-Yr. Warranty and a Reverse Osmosis Water Softener system conveys! Stand alone garage built in 2018. It could get converted into an ADU or added onto to make a larger ADU. Extra large back yard could also accommodate a pool!- - Imperial Beach is happening! Enjoy a great meal with views of the Pier at The Brigantine, Stunning sunsets at the Pier South Marriott with Sea 180°, a restaurant on the sand, Mike Hess Brewery, which is hopping 7-days/week and has an upper deck with ocean views, Coronado Brewing Co. with a deck, Bikeway Village and the new Novo Brewery with views out to Coronado! Family friendly Pizza Port is now open and the Seacoast Marketplace is under construction and Coming Soon! IB is a fun and friendly community. Popular, year-round festivities include the Farmer's Market, the Sun and Sea Festival - Sand Castle Competition, and IronMan Super Frog Triathlon!
